//////////////////
Package.json 
> Entry point to the app
> Command to start test build the application
> All the packages we are using
> MetaData (name,version,description)

////////////////////////////////
Step to generate packages.json
------------------------------
* Nodejs Must be installed in your system
> open the cmd and go inside the folder
> npm init
> Answer all questions
> type "yes"
******Alternate*****
> npm init -y

Step to install Local `packages
------------------------------
* Nodejs Must be installed in your system
> open the cmd and go inside the folder
> npm i packagesName  / npm install packagesName

//// Type of Dependency ////
Local Dependency 
> By default packages installed is called as local dependencies

Global Dependency
> Can be used by any application
> It installed in the laptop
> need admin permission 
> they will not add in packages.json
> Only use to start the app

Dev Dependency
> Dependency that we require only at the time of development
npm i --save-dev packageName


package-lock.json >> dependencies tree
node_modules> where all packages install locally
